    "content_hash": "b25719022af73c7b",
    "department": "Product",
    "description": "WHY CLIPBOARD EXISTS:\n\nWe exist to lift as many people up the socioeconomic ladder as possible. We dramatically improve lives by letting professionals turn extra time and ambition into career growth and financial opportunity. We achieve this with our app-based marketplace that connects workplaces and professionals, allowing professionals to book on-demand shifts and workplaces to access on-demand talent.\n\n\nABOUT CLIPBOARD:\n\nClipboard is a fast-growing Series C marketplace. We are a leader in our Long Term Care vertical and are expanding into several others (Dental, Home Health, etc.), as well as building out a full-time product.\nWe are a YC Top Company https://www.ycombinator.com/topcompanies/ with a global, remote team of 1,000+ people. We have been profitable since 2022, and fill millions of shifts annually at partner workplaces across the U.S., where tens of thousands of professionals work with us every year.\nWe are looking for your help to keep growing so we can serve more professionals and workplaces.\n\nTo learn more about us, take a look at our website here https://www.clipboardhealth.com/careers.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nThe Account Manager will be instrumental in helping grow and retain Clipboard's existing markets. Healthcare providers are core to the Clipboard marketplace — the Account Manager is in charge of nurturing and expanding relationships with current users, going deep with those users to understand their needs, and ensuring they're consistently successful on the platform. There's no ceiling to what you can achieve in this role — if you're highly motivated to go above and beyond, a diligent executor, and a strong written/verbal communicator, Clipboard is the place for you to excel.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n - Managing and growing relationships with an existing portfolio of healthcare providers and dental offices\n\n - Clearly articulating the value proposition of the app to current users to drive continued engagement and expansion\n\n - Going deep with healthcare providers and dental offices to uncover their evolving needs, understand their challenges, and find ways to genuinely help them succeed on the platform\n\n - Establishing credibility and rapport with providers, which includes demonstrating a strong understanding of the app\n\n - Being the go-to point of contact for users that need help navigating the app, resolving issues, and getting the most out of the platform\n\n - Helping fill new and urgent shifts in your assigned markets\n\nQualifications\n\n - Willingness to hustle / lack of fear\n\n - Experience texting, emailing, and talking with English-speaking clients and prospects\n\nRequirements\n\n - Stable high-speed internet connection\n\n - A computer workstation (laptop or desktop)\n\n - Internationally located (not in the US or Canada)\n\n - Availability to work US working hours\n\n - Fluency in English speaking and writing\n\nBeyond the Basics — What Will Make You Successful\n\n - Noticing \u0026 Curiosity — You pick up on things others miss and ask \"why\" more than once because the first answer is rarely the whole story. You dig to understand the root of a problem or situation rather than accepting things at face value, and you're constantly updating your understanding of the customers you serve.\n\n - Initiative \u0026 Persistence — You have a bias for action. You know that our customers are dealing with real problems today, and you don't wait for perfect information before making a move. You're scrappy and self-reliant, you find ways through obstacles rather than around them, and you bring solutions instead of asking \"what should I do?\"\n\n - Ownership — The buck stops with you, no matter what anyone else did or did not do. You take full responsibility for your results, fix problems when you see them — even outside your immediate area — and put processes in place to make sure those problems don't happen again.\n\n - Customer-Centric — You feel your customers' situations genuinely and care about improving their lives, not just hitting a number. Talking to customers and solving their problems isn't a task on your list — it's the job.\n\n - Humble — You're low ego and care about getting to the best outcome, not about being right. You readily admit when you don't know something, you actively seek out feedback, and you're always looking to become a better version of yourself.\n\nBenefits\n\n - Do great work that matters for customers who could really use your help\n\n - Competitive pay\n\n - Unlimited PTO\n\n - Fully Remote\n\nEstimated annual compensation: $12,000–$15,600 USD. Each candidate's compensation offer within this range will be based on multiple factors including, but not limited to, relevant education, qualifications, certifications, experience, and geographic location.\n\nQuick Note on Scammers:\n\nClipboard would never ask you for money or your bank details to participate in our hiring process. Report any scammers impersonating the Clipboard hiring team members here https://forms.gle/SyGaxHFbon7Hg9fW6.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
